<paragraph blockId="17.[801,1452,1207,1455]" pageId="17" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis box="[839,897,1208,1231]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="172">Notes</emphasis>
. – A specimen of this widespread Asian species (“Planta Ind. Orient. Loliamanta dicta”) is in L (L-908.352- 522); Houttuyn did not discuss it. The vernacular name does not seem to be Malayan / Javanese, so it may have come from 
<collectingCountry box="[801,884,1335,1359]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="17" pageNumber="172">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
. A Thunberg collection from Java (UPS-THUNB n° 14593) bears what is presumably another vernacular name, “Noka nanta” (or a huge misreading?), and is therefore probably not a duplicate.
</paragraph>
